Nelson Mandela Bay council speaker, Jonathan Lawack has been removed through a vote of no confidence. 60 councilors voted in favour and 59 opposed.  United Democratic Movement (UDM) councillor, Mongameli Bobani tabled the motion to remove Lawack at a council meeting in Port Elizabeth. It was seconded by the Economic Freedom Fightersâ€™ (EFF) Zilindile Vena who has submitted a motion of no confidence against mayor Athol Trollip. Bobani says opposition parties have lost confidence in the speaker due to his allegedly being bias towards the DA.